<task id="096" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Dispatch memory.promotion_pending from MatterMemoryPromotionService</title>
    <phase>4: WP5 6-Tier Memory Subsystem (sub-WP 4e)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>093,094,095</dependencies>
    <blocks>098</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, services, ADR-030</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include 'bff-api'; modifies `.cs`; ADR-030 v2 binding (memory channel + payload shape); ADR-015 binding (factSummary 80-char preview only)</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>4-L</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add dispatch of `memory.promotion_pending` PaneEventBus event from `MatterMemoryPromotionService.QueueForApprovalAsync` (after successful Cosmos pending-record write). Payload: `{ type: 'promotion_pending', promotionId, factSummary (80-char preview), matterId, sessionId }` per architecture §6.4 + ADR-030 v2 amendment 2026-06-21. Uses the new `memory` channel (added to PaneEventTypes by task 060). ADR-015 binding: `factSummary` is the ONLY content field permitted and is capped at 80 characters; full fact content NEVER emitted in the event.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in PaneEventBus dispatch + ADR-015 tier-1 payload safety.</role>

  <goal>
    `MatterMemoryPromotionService.QueueForApprovalAsync` (task 093) extended to emit `memory.promotion_pending` after the Cosmos write completes. The dispatch goes through the existing server-side event emitter (e.g., `IContextEventEmitter` or whichever channel emits to PaneEventBus). Payload schema MATCHES the architecture §6.4 + spec FR-32 contract verbatim. Unit tests assert: event emitted after Cosmos write success; payload shape exact; `factSummary` capped ≤80 chars (substring of fact, no full fact in payload); event NOT emitted on Cosmos write failure.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §6.4 (promote-to-matter flow — `memory.promotion_pending` emission), ADR-030 v2 amendment (memory channel added by task 060), ADR-015 (factSummary 80-char preview only; never full fact). Spec FR-32 specifies the channel + payload verbatim. The frontend subscriber (task 098) consumes this event via `usePaneEvent('memory', ...)`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/MatterMemoryPromotionService.cs (from task 093)</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-030-pane-event-bus.md (v2 amendment)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">No new endpoint.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Inject existing event-emitter contract directly into the service (likely already wired by task 093).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Service is BFF-internal; event emitter is in the AI eventing namespace — no PublicContracts crossing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">CRITICAL — `factSummary` is the ONLY content-bearing field and MUST be truncated to ≤80 chars. Full fact text MUST NOT appear in the event payload. Telemetry logs also omit fact content per tier-1 rule.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">≤+0.05 MB delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">v2 amendment: `memory` channel is the canonical channel for memory-domain events. Use `memory.promotion_pending` discriminant. Do NOT route through `workspace.*` channels (architecture §6.4 + ADR-030 v2).</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§6.4 — event emitted AFTER Cosmos pending-write succeeds; not on failure.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture">§6.4 — payload schema: `{ type: 'promotion_pending', promotionId, factSummary (80-char preview), matterId, sessionId }`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/architecture/stateful-chat-architecture.md</file>
