      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load architecture §6.4 + ADR-030 v2 + ADR-015.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `MatterMemoryPromotionService.cs` (from task 093) — locate the `QueueForApprovalAsync` success path right after the Cosmos write.</step>
    <step order="3">Identify the canonical server-side event emitter (likely `IContextEventEmitter` or a dedicated PaneEventBus contract — search `Services/Ai/Audit/` and `Services/Ai/Eventing/` for the pattern).</step>
    <step order="4">Add emit logic: `factSummary` = `fact.Substring(0, Math.Min(80, fact.Length))`; payload `{ type: "promotion_pending", promotionId, factSummary, matterId, sessionId }`; channel `"memory"`.</step>
    <step order="5">If the channel string constant doesn't exist server-side, add `MemoryEventChannel = "memory"` to the appropriate constants file mirroring the `workspace`/`context` channel patterns.</step>
    <step order="6">Update unit tests at `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Memory/MatterMemoryPromotionServiceTests.cs` (extended from task 093):
      - Assert event emitted after Cosmos write success
      - Assert `factSummary.Length &lt;= 80`
      - Assert event payload shape matches architecture §6.4
      - Assert event NOT emitted when Cosmos write throws
    </step>
    <step order="7">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`. Must pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Measure BFF publish-size delta; write `notes/handoffs/096-bff-publish-delta.md`.</step>
    <step order="9">Run code-review + adr-check (Step 9.5 FULL — adr-check is binding for ADR-015 fact-content rule).</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 096 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">MatterMemoryPromotionService, event emitter contracts</tool>
